  - dia_id
  - turn_index_global
  - text
  - voice_style
  - modality_available
  - notes_for_dataset_builder
- audio_id is optional. It may be null or an empty string when no audio file exists.
- voice_style must be short and purely observable.
- Good voice_style content:
  - pace
  - pause length
  - emphasis on a word
  - volume or softness
  - clipped ending
  - trailing off
  - flatter sentence ending
  - tighter articulation on technical words
- Do not use emotion labels, interpretations, attitudes, or answer-like cues in voice_style.
- If audio_id is null or empty, do not include "audio" in modality_available.
- Prefer modality_available to be ["text", "voice_style"] when only text plus delivery description are available.
- Only include "audio" in modality_available when a real audio reference is present.
- notes_for_dataset_builder is for internal generation support only.
- Do NOT include emotion labels or gold answers in the conversation JSON.
- Keep linked_event_ids sparse and meaningful; do not attach events to every turn mechanically.
- At least some student turns should be marked as candidate emotion anchors.
- At least some turns should be marked as candidate fact anchors.
- Spread candidate emotion anchors and fact anchors across multiple sessions rather than concentrating them near the end.
- Keep the blueprint-specific teacher-student mismatch legible through wording choices and response patterns.
- Session count, session ordering, and total turn count must match the input blueprint exactly.

